2026-04-30T05:44:37.1420714Z           "after": "8d64891f4752aea55d88cddb6c5b6f58b984206f",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1421298Z           "base_ref": null,
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1421917Z           "before": "03c22823f4ae9828a4c0c9998615cf366e2512a8",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1422460Z           "commits": [
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1422978Z             {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1423398Z               "author": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1423871Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1424391Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1424915Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1425420Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1425853Z               "committer": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1426464Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1426946Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1427405Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1427963Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1428493Z               "distinct": false,
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1428987Z               "id": "a6e4140dc599fec4883f3a8eb8c292ff816de581",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1433868Z               "message": "Add lightweight token auth and refactor CacheDir to DataDir\n\nWeb UI and APIs are now gated behind a token-based auth scheme. A single\nroot user (username 'ednsv') is identified by a hash configured via the\nEDNSV_AUTH_TOKEN_HASH env var (or AuthTokenHash in appsettings.json). Set\nthe value to \"none\" (the default) to disable auth entirely.\n\nHash format is base64url(sha256(utf8-bytes(token))) with no padding, so\nadmins can compute it with stock openssl/basenc without an extra tool.\n\nAuthenticated users with can_issue may mint additional tokens through a\nnew /tokens.html page, recorded in {DataDir}/auth/users.json with the\nissuer, IP, and timestamp. Revoking a token cascades to every token that\nuser (or their sub-issuers) ever issued. Users only see their own\ndescendants in the listing; root sees the full tree.\n\nThe middleware accepts both Authorization: *** for scripts and\nAuthorization: Basic ednsv:<token> for browsers (which get the native\nlogin dialog and pass the header automatically on subsequent fetches).\n\nCacheDir has been replaced by DataDir, with cache/ and auth/ subfolders\ncreated automatically.",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1438006Z               "timestamp": "2026-04-30T03:47:06Z",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1439125Z               "tree_id": "2d4085f37c5b0be7672e22e32feec53dc9e78aa8",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1439862Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/a6e4140dc599fec4883f3a8eb8c292ff816de581"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1440273Z             },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1440571Z             {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1440779Z               "author": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1463465Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1463976Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1464383Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1464765Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1465037Z               "committer": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1465349Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1465645Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1465897Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1466240Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1466530Z               "distinct": false,
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1466915Z               "id": "857c3a496a65ce5dc80c67f6b1301708fb062373",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1469056Z               "message": "Send WWW-Authenticate as separate headers per scheme\n\nBrowsers don't reliably parse two challenges on a single comma-separated\nWWW-Authenticate line — the parameter comma collides with the challenge\nseparator, so Chrome/Firefox skipped the Basic login prompt and just\nrendered the JSON body. Emitting one header per scheme is the\nconformant fix.",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1470317Z               "timestamp": "2026-04-30T04:03:31Z",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1470622Z               "tree_id": "af882ddee22a19bc2f51d361d1d56bf69d280aa3",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1471086Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/857c3a496a65ce5dc80c67f6b1301708fb062373"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1471460Z             },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1471621Z             {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1471783Z               "author": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1472020Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1472268Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1472480Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1472682Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1472857Z               "committer": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1473082Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1473333Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1473542Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1473739Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1473918Z               "distinct": false,
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1474171Z               "id": "b1d5454ef733fe6ef90bca451cba9014a968e990",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1476057Z               "message": "Return HTML body on 401 for browser navigations\n\nChrome (and some other browsers) suppress the native Basic-auth login\nprompt when the 401 response body is application/json — they treat it\nas a data response and render the JSON instead of showing the dialog.\nSniff the Accept header and return a minimal HTML body for browser\nnavigations; keep the JSON shape for API clients.\n\nAlso add Cache-Control: no-store so a successful login isn't blocked\nby a cached 401.",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1477580Z               "timestamp": "2026-04-30T04:08:03Z",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1477882Z               "tree_id": "a6fe4cbf729df0a32a1cfda26acc54e0a313ca2e",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1478988Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/b1d5454ef733fe6ef90bca451cba9014a968e990"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1479579Z             },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1479852Z             {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1480024Z               "author": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1480246Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1480497Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1480702Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1480909Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1481075Z               "committer": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1481294Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1481534Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1481745Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1481942Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1482120Z               "distinct": false,
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1482364Z               "id": "1c6572753f73cbb549fc1bacb6b83efb695298ed",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1483768Z               "message": "Advertise Basic only (not Bearer) on 401s for browser navigations\n\nSome browsers see *** the challenge list, attempt to use it, fail\nsilently because they don't natively support it, and never fall back to\nthe Basic prompt. Drop *** the response when the request looks\nlike a browser navigation; API clients still get both schemes.",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1484898Z               "timestamp": "2026-04-30T04:13:33Z",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1485206Z               "tree_id": "a593b86af827e1db2c2fbd17174101d5365b1997",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1485642Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/1c6572753f73cbb549fc1bacb6b83efb695298ed"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1486030Z             },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1486199Z             {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1486364Z               "author": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1486588Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1486830Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1487077Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1487282Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1487458Z               "committer": {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1487673Z                 "email": "noreply@anthropic.com",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1487922Z                 "name": "Claude",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1488282Z                 "username": "claude"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1488595Z               },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1488774Z               "distinct": false,
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1489023Z               "id": "38a20712c7abd0b0863f75a48feea7121aaf345c",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1492801Z               "message": "Replace browser Basic auth with login page + HttpOnly cookie\n\nBrowser Basic auth turned out to be unreliable in Edge (and increasingly\nrestricted across Chromium overall) — the login dialog wouldn't appear\neven with conformant WWW-Authenticate headers. Switch the browser flow\nto a plain /login.html page that POSTs credentials to /api/auth/login;\non success the server responds with an HttpOnly, SameSite=Strict,\nSecure-when-HTTPS cookie holding the raw token. The cookie is validated\non each request via the existing AuthenticateBearer path, so revoking\na user immediately invalidates their cookie too — no separate session\nstore.\n\nBearer (and Basic) Authorization headers still work for API/CLI access.\nUnauthenticated browser navigations get a 302 to /login.html; API\nclients still get 401 + JSON. /login.html and /api/auth/login are now\nthe only public paths.\n\nAdds a \"Sign out\" link on index.html and tokens.html that POSTs to\n/api/auth/logout and redirects back to the login page.",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1496078Z               "timestamp": "2026-04-30T04:42:57Z",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1496369Z               "tree_id": "33ed97ebac5b511b065bdd55a630da1a851de0b1",
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1496818Z               "url": "https://github.com/pkinerd/ednsv/commit/38a20712c7abd0b0863f75a48feea7121aaf345c"
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1497184Z             },
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1497346Z             {
2026-04-30T05:44:37.1497503Z               "author": {
